&amp;ldquo;Ami Opowiada&amp;rdquo; was my first significant app release on Google Play. It was a platformer that told the story of Ami, who traveled through fantastical lands. The game achieved over 54,000 unique installs, received positive reviews, and generated a substantial amount of revenue through ads. Although the game is no longer available to players for various reasons, and I no longer support it, it was a fascinating project.&lt;/p></description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="/published-games/1727103498202-ami-opowiada/featured.png"/></item><item><title>MVC Pattern and Snake</title><link>/personal-projects/1727103417339-unity-mvc-snake/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Feb 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/personal-projects/1727103417339-unity-mvc-snake/</guid><description>&lt;h2 class="relative group">Using the MVP Pattern in Unity for the Snake Game
